reviewText:
Oddworld: New 'n' Tasty is a remake of the good ol' game Oddworld: Abe's Oddysee, and I'm not exaggerating when I say it's the best remake of a game ever done.
New 'n' Tasty isn't just a simple remake: it adds a lot more as well. Now you don't have to rescue 99 Mudokons, but 299!
New cool things include:
- Screen which scrolls along with you;
- New, very comfortable control scheme;
- Leaderboards;
- New sound effects and voices;
- A lot of other amazing things.
The graphics and models are extremely well made, and they look just like the old sprites, but in 3D and HQ. If you have a weak laptop/PC, you'll be able to adjust the quality of everything, so you can still play it (coming from a 1.8ghz, 4GB RAM Laptop)! And don't worry that the game will look ugly if you put everything on the lowest settings, because the game will still look pretty!
New 'N' Tasty recreates all levels very accuratelly, and they're a lot more fun to play now!

For this review, I just cannot find words for the game. This is the best game of 2015 to me so far. I loved every single moment of it, and I'm looking forward to 100% it and get all the achievements.

It's a MASTERPIECE!
